   <concept id="FAR_12_503">
      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph class="- topic/ph " props="autonumber">12.503</ph> 
         Applicability of certain
laws to Executive agency contracts for the acquisition of commercial
products and commercial services.
      </title>
      <conbody>
         <ol id="d711e13">
            <li>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e10">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                   The following laws are not applicable
to Executive agency contracts for the acquisition of commercial products or commercial
services:
               </p>
               <ol>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e16">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/link/uscode/10/983?type=usc&amp;year=mostrecent&amp;link-type=html"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">10 U.S.C. 983</xref>, Institutions
of Higher Education that Prevent ROTC Access or Military Recruiting
on Campus: Denial of Grants and Contracts from Department of Defense,
Department of Education, and Certain Other Departments and Agencies
(see <xref href="9.110.dita#FAR_9_110" outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">9.110</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e26">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        <xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/link/uscode/31/1354?type=usc&amp;year=mostrecent&amp;link-type=html"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">31 U.S.C. 1354(a)</xref>,
Limitation on Use of Appropriated Funds for Contracts with Entities
Not Meeting Veterans' Employment Reporting Requirements (see <xref href="22.1302.dita#FAR_22_1302" outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">22.1302</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e36">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        <xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/link/uscode/41/1708?type=usc&amp;year=mostrecent&amp;link-type=html"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">41 U.S.C. 1708(e)(3)</xref>,
Minimum Response Time for Offers (see <xref href="5.203.dita#FAR_5_203"
                              base="i1120755"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">5.203</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e46">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        <xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/link/uscode/41/2303?type=usc&amp;year=mostrecent&amp;link-type=html"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">41 U.S.C. 2303(b)</xref>,
Policy on Personal Conflicts of Interest by Contractor Employees
(see <xref href="Subpart_3.11.dita#FAR_Subpart_3_11" outputclass="fm:Subpart">subpartÂ  3.11</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e56">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(5)</ph>
                        <xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/link/uscode/41/3901?type=usc&amp;year=mostrecent&amp;link-type=html"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">41 U.S.C. 3901(b)</xref> and <xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/link/uscode/10/2306?type=usc&amp;year=mostrecent&amp;link-type=html"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">10 U.S.C. 2306(b)</xref>,
Contingent Fees (see <xref href="3.404.dita#FAR_3_404" outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">3.404</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e69">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(6)</ph>
                        <xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/link/uscode/41/4706?type=usc&amp;year=mostrecent&amp;link-type=html"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">41 U.S.C. 4706(d)(1)</xref> and <xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/link/uscode/10/2313?type=usc&amp;year=mostrecent&amp;link-type=html"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">10 U.S.C. 2313(c)(1)</xref>,
GAO Access to Contractor Employees, section 871 of Public Law 110-417
(see <xref href="52.214-26.dita#FAR_52_214_26"
                              base="FAR_52_214_26"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">52.214-26</xref> and <xref href="52.212-2.dita#FAR_52_212_2"
                              base="i1060530"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">52.212-2</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e85">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(7)</ph>
                         41 U.S.C.
chapter 65, Contracts for Materials, Supplies, Articles, and Equipment
Exceeding $10,000 (see subpart 22.6).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e90">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(8)</ph>
                         41 U.S.C.
chapter 81, Drug-Free Workplace (see <xref href="23.501.dita#FAR_23_501"
                              base="i1094542"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">23.501</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e98">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(9)</ph>
                         Section
806(a)(3) of Public Law 102-190, as amended by sections 2091 and
8105 of Public Law 103-355 (<xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/link/uscode/10/2302?type=usc&amp;year=mostrecent&amp;link-type=html"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">10 U.S.C. 2302 note</xref>),
Payment Protections for Subcontractors and Suppliers (see <xref href="28.106-6.dita#FAR_28_106_6"
                              base="i1088884"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">28.106-6</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e109">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(10)</ph>
                        <ph rev="FAC 2022-08 October 28, 2022"><?FM MARKER [CaseNumber] FAR Case 2018-020?>
                           <xref href="https://www.govinfo.gov/link/uscode/15/644"
                                 format="html"
                                 scope="external">15 U.S.C.
                              644(w)</xref>, Solicitation Notice Regarding
                           Administration of Change Orders for Construction (see
                              <xref href="36.211.dita#FAR_36_211" outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">36.211</xref>).<?FM MARKER [Why] Amend section 12.503 by adding paragraph (a)(10)?></ph>
                     </p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph> Certain
                  requirements of the following laws are not applicable to
                  executive agency contracts for the acquisition of commercial
                  products and commercial services: </p>
               <ol id="d711e174">
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e115">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=granuleid:USC-prelim-title22-section2593a&amp;num=0&amp;edition=prelim"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">22 U.S.C. 2593e</xref>, Requirement
for a certification under Measures Against Persons Involved in Activities
that Violate Arms Control Treaties or Agreements with the United
States (see <xref href="9.109.dita#FAR_9_109" outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">9.109</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e125">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">40 U.S.C.chapter 37</xref>,
Requirement for a certificate and clause under the Contract Work
Hours and Safety Standards statute (see <xref href="22.305.dita#FAR_22_305"
                              base="i1098333"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">22.305</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e135">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">41 U.S.C.8703</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">8703</xref>, Requirement
for a clause and certain other requirements related to kickbacks
(see <xref href="3.502.dita#FAR_3_502"
                              base="i1124348"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">3.502</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e148">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">49 U.S.C.40118</xref>, Requirement
for a clause under the Fly American provisions (see <xref href="47.405.dita#FAR_47_405"
                              base="i1070062"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">47.405</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li>
               <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e158">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                   The applicability
of the following laws have been modified in regard to Executive
agency contracts for the acquisition of commercial products and
commercial services:
               </p>
               <ol id="d711e234">
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e164">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">41 U.S.C.4704</xref> and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">10 U.S.C.2402</xref>, Prohibition
on Limiting Subcontractor Direct Sales to the United States (see <xref href="3.503.dita#FAR_3_503"
                              base="i1124393"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">3.503</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e177">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">41 U.S.C.chapter 35,</xref> Truthful
Cost or Pricing Data, and <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">10 U.S.C.2306a</xref>, Truth
in Negotiations Act (see <xref href="15.403.dita#FAR_15_403"
                              base="i1105934"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">15.403</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                     <p class="- topic/p " id="d738e190">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external">41 U.S.C.chapter 15</xref>,
Cost Accounting Standards (48 CFR Chapter 99) (see <xref href="12.214.dita#FAR_12_214"
                              base="i1113603"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly">12.214</xref>).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
